
Manager
RECEIVED
1) ignore the containers
{
	'command' : 'container_ignore',
	'containerID' : '.........'
}

2) set the threshold
{
	'command' : 'container_threshold',
	'threshold': '5'
}

3) get the containers status
{
	'command' : 'give_content'
}

SENT[to the controller]
1) update notification
{
	'command' : 'update',
	'address' : '172.16.0.2'
}

2) sending the list of the containers with the status
{
	'command' : 'give_content',
	'address' : '172.16.0.2'
}

3) notify to the controller that the manager is active
{
	'command' : 'live',
	'address' : '172.16.0.2'
}


-> shutdown it 
    -> send to the controller 'update'

-> when manager detect that the container is restarted 
    -> send to the controller 'update'		

Antagonist
if u have already an idea for structure of the messages u can put it here
